WEBVTT

00:00:56.831 --> 00:01:00.751
In fact, this spring, he published
a searing critique of Facebook

00:01:00.775 --> 00:01:03.679
and his one-time friend, Mark Zuckerberg,

00:01:03.703 --> 00:01:06.728
the book cleverly titled "Zucked."

00:01:07.307 --> 00:01:09.505
So Roger has had something
of an inside view

00:01:09.529 --> 00:01:12.878
of what he considers to be
an unfolding catastrophe,

00:01:12.902 --> 00:01:16.401
and has teamed up with other critics
to press for radical changes,

00:01:16.425 --> 00:01:20.307
including government regulation,
and even antitrust action.

00:01:21.092 --> 00:01:22.610
So this was a fantastic chance

00:01:22.634 --> 00:01:25.964
to really dig into two
of the biggest questions of the moment.

00:01:26.411 --> 00:01:31.442
Namely, how did the big, beautiful
dream of technology connecting the world